"Then Pyrrhus thus: ¢ Go thou from me to fate, And to my father my foul deeds relate. 2 Now dic!—With that he dragg’d the tremblingsire, Sliddering through clotter'd blood and holy mire, (The mingled paste his murder'd son had made) Haul'd from beneath the violated shade, % And on the sacred pile the royal victim laid. His right hand held his bloody falchion bare,"